The United States has condemned the killing of Laurent DuPasquier, an International Committee of the Red Cross (ICRC) staff member, who was killed by shelling near the ICRC's premises in Donetsk, Ukraine. The US extends its sympathies and condolences to Mr. DuPasquier's family, friends, and colleagues. They call on all parties involved in the conflict to respect international humanitarian law and ensure that the ICRC and other humanitarian organizations are protected as they provide aid to civilians in Ukraine. The US also urges the parties to protect civilians and hold accountable those who engage in indiscriminate use of force. They express appreciation for the ICRC and other humanitarians who put themselves in harm's way to alleviate suffering in times of war.